OL,3,CVote counting due to begin in Scottish
OL,4,CParliament election
OL,6,FVote counting in the Scottish
OL,7,FParliament election is due to begin on
OL,8,FFriday morning, after the country went
OL,9,Fto the polls on Thursday.
OL,11,FBallot boxes will be opened at 9am at
OL,12,Fdesignated counting centres across
OL,13,FScotland.
OL,15,FThe first constituencies are expected
OL,16,Fto be declared around midday, with
OL,17,Ffurther results coming in during the
OL,18,Fafternoon and evening.
OL,20,FThe full picture of the results should
OL,21,Fbecome clear on Friday evening.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G1/8
